body:
`main.js`:

```js
import './lib'
```

`lib.js` version 1 ([playground link](https://rollupjs.org/repl?version=0.47.6&)):

```js
function first() {
  for (let i = -1;;++i) {}
  second
}

function second() {}
```

`lib.js` version 2 ([playground link](https://rollupjs.org/repl?version=0.47.6&)):

```js
function first() {
  ++i
  second
}

function second() {}
```

In both cases, the `main` output is:

```js
function second() {}
```

Expected output: empty. Removing the `++` or replacing it with `i += 1` bizarrely solves the problem.
